Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of memory networks and relation networks, which are popular techniques in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results, which suggests that the authors may have used machine learning algorithms such as deep learning, which are often discussed in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision) since it deals with text-based reasoning, which is often used in image captioning and other computer vision tasks.
